"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Fix: Resume fetches metadata branch when not available locally\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nWhen running `entire resume` on a repo where `entire/checkpoints/v1` doesn't exist locally (e.g., after a fresh clone), the single-checkpoint path in `resumeFromCurrentBranch()` calls `strategy.GetMetadataBranchTree(repo)` directly. When that fails, it falls through to `checkRemoteMetadata()`, which only checks the remote tracking ref (`origin/entire/checkpoints/v1`) — but that ref also doesn't exist if no fetch has ever been done. Result: the user sees the unhelpful error:\\n\\n```\\nCheckpoint '564aea6f7ca5' found in commit but session metadata not available\\nThe entire/checkpoints/v1 branch may not exist locally or on the remote.\\n```\\n\\nMeanwhile, the multi-checkpoint path (squash merges) correctly uses `getMetadataTree()` which has a full fallback chain: local → treeless fetch → full fetch → remote tree.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Fix single-checkpoint path in `resumeFromCurrentBranch` (`cmd/entire/cli/resume.go`)\\n\\n**Lines 177-185**: Replace `strategy.GetMetadataBranchTree(repo)` + `checkRemoteMetadata` fallback with `getMetadataTree(ctx, repo)`:\\n\\n```go\\n// Before:\\nif metadataTree == nil {\\n    var err error\\n    metadataTree, err = strategy.GetMetadataBranchTree(repo)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return checkRemoteMetadata(ctx, repo, checkpointID)\\n    }\\n}\\n\\n// After:\\nif metadataTree == nil {\\n    var err error\\n    metadataTree, err = getMetadataTree(ctx, repo)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return checkRemoteMetadata(ctx, repo, checkpointID)\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis makes the single-checkpoint path use the same treeless-fetch → full-fetch fallback chain as the multi-checkpoint path. The `checkRemoteMetadata` fallback is preserved for when all fetch attempts fail.\\n\\n### 2. Ensure metadata is fresh when branch exists locally (`cmd/entire/cli/resume.go`)\\n\\nAdd a fetch-and-update step in `getMetadataTree()` so that even when the local branch exists, we update it from remote to have the latest data. The current code returns early on local success, which can return stale data if the remote has newer checkpoints.\\n\\nUpdate `getMetadataTree()` to always attempt a treeless fetch to update the local branch, falling back to the existing local tree if the fetch fails:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc getMetadataTree(ctx context.Context, repo *git.Repository) (*object.Tree, error) {\\n    // Always try treeless fetch first to ensure local branch is up-to-date\\n    if fetchErr := FetchMetadataTreeOnly(ctx); fetchErr == nil {\\n        metadataTree, err := strategy.GetMetadataBranchTree(repo)\\n        if err == nil {\\n            return metadataTree, nil\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    // Try local (may have been set by a prior fetch or push)\\n    metadataTree, err := strategy.GetMetadataBranchTree(repo)\\n    if err == nil {\\n        return metadataTree, nil\\n    }\\n\\n    // Fallback: full fetch from remote\\n    if fetchErr := FetchMetadataBranch(ctx); fetchErr == nil {\\n        metadataTree, err = strategy.GetMetadataBranchTree(repo)\\n        if err == nil {\\n            return metadataTree, nil\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    // Try remote tree directly\\n    remoteTree, remoteErr := strategy.GetRemoteMetadataBranchTree(repo)\\n    if remoteErr != nil {\\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"metadata branch not available: %w\\\", remoteErr)\\n    }\\n    return remoteTree, nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Add E2E test (`e2e/tests/resume_remote_test.go`)\\n\\nNew E2E test file testing resume when the metadata branch doesn't exist locally:\\n\\n**Test: `TestResumeFromClonedRepo`**\\n1. Agent creates a file on feature branch, user commits → checkpoint created\\n2. Push feature branch and metadata branch to bare remote (`SetupBareRemote`)\\n3. Clone the repo to a new directory (simulating a teammate cloning)\\n4. Delete the local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch 